txt.en:
'Oh, don't worry about me, dear. I'm just resting; these old bones protest when I don't take a break. Carrying these sacks to my waggon is exhausting work, and I've still got to deliver them!

'All that's left are the harvests from Mileth and Lothwen; the sacks are ready to be collected outside their homes. If you are willing, would you bring those sacks to me?

'How about you visit Mileth first? Her home is north-west from here.'
You have delivered all requested crops to Annaben.\n\nYou should talk to her.
Annaben has asked you to pick up a sack of crops from Lothwen's home.\n\nHer home in Glaniath is west of Annaben's waggon.
It's Annaben's job to collect the harvest from the Glaniath farmers, but the work has proven to be more than she expected.
'How about you visit Mileth first? Her home is north-west from here.'
'Lothwen's home is west from here. Just a bit more walking left to do!'
'Thank you, my dear. I'll be sending these crops to nearby towns that weren't as fortuitous as Glaniath was during the war. I'm sure the townsfolk will appreciate your hard work!'
Annaben has asked you to pick up a sack of crops from Mileth's home.\n\nHer home in Glaniath is north-west of Annaben's waggon.
'Oh, bless you. Lothwen's crops are next!'
Pick up a sack of crops from Lothwen's home
Pick up a sack of crops from Mileth's home
